    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Harris Drury Cohen Shifting Executives</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Allison Fass</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Fass, Allison</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Phil Cohen will step down as managing partner at Harris Drury Cohen; Michael Goldberg will assume new post of chief executive; Stan Harris, creative partner, will add new post of chairman; Norm Tousignant will become chief operating officer, a new post (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Harris Drury Cohen in Fort Lauderdale, Fla., is reorganizing top management.</p>
        <p>Phil Cohen, 54, will step down as managing partner to concentrate on account and strategic management for clients like Bombadier and Prestige Brands. Michael Goldberg, 35, will assume the new post of chief executive; he had been group account leader.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Harris Drury Cohen in Fort Lauderdale, Fla., is reorganizing top management.</p>
        <p>Phil Cohen, 54, will step down as managing partner to concentrate on account and strategic management for clients like Bombadier and Prestige Brands. Michael Goldberg, 35, will assume the new post of chief executive; he had been group account leader.</p>
        <p>Stan Harris, 52, creative partner, will add the new post of chairman. Norm Tousignant, 46, chief financial officer, will become chief operating officer, a new post. Two executives will continue in their current duties: Michael Cannon, 43, executive creative leader, and Norm Olson, 56, leader for media services.</p>
        <p>THE MEDIA BUSINESS: ADVERTISING -- ADDENDA</p>
      </block>
